Figure 4: The heatmap shows degree of repetition in responses to open-ended queries generated Dy the same LMs. For each model, we generate 50 responses per query across 100 open-ended queries from INFINITY-CHATI1OO. We then compute the average pairwise sentence embedding similarities for each query's response pool and measure the percentage of queries falling into the similarity ranges indicated on the y-axis. Under the sampling parameters (top-p = 0.9, temperature = 1.0), the average pairwise similarity among responses to the same prompt typically exceeds 0.8. As a baseline, randomly paired responses from the global pool 100% fall within the 0.1-0.2 range.
